      "content": "i get the systemic argument, but what about the literature that focuses more on the biological or evolutionary psychology side of things? there are researchers who argue there might be hereditary components or innate differences in impulse control or cognitive traits that align with certain populations. can u summarize the main arguments and data points used by proponents of those theories to explain the gap?",
